Target: OntoSpecies is an ontology developed for representing chemical species.

Comment: "An ensemble of chemically identical molecular entities" (McNaught & Wilkinson, 1997).
A chemical formula that indicates the relative number of each constituting chemical element of a species or molecular entity.
A combined representation of a number indicating the amount of an element in a species and the element.
An atom or isotope.
The address of a web page that describes a resource.
The mass of one mole of a species in units of g/mol.
The overall net charge of a molecule or ion in units of elementary charge.
A chemical compound formula expressing the number of atoms of each element present in a compound, without indicating how they are linked.
The energy required to form 1 mole of a substance from its constituent elements.
A measure of the average amount of energy of motion, or kinetic energy, a system contains" (Chemistry LibreTexts, accessed on 11/11/2019).
A relation between a species or molecular entity and the chemical formula describing the relative number of each constituting chemical element of the species or molecular entity.
A relation between a species or molecular entity and the total mass of one mole of this species or molecular entity in g/mol
A relation between a species or molecular entity and the overall net charge of this species or molecular entity in units of elementary charge
A relation that defines that a species or molecular entity contains a chemical element.
A relation that defines a combined representation of a number indicating the amount of an element in a species and the element.
A relation that defines the number of atoms of a given element contained in a species or molecular entity.
A relation between a species or molecular entity and the chemical formula describing the number of atoms of each constituting chemical element of the species or molecular entity.
A relation that defines the standard enthalpy of formation of a given species.
A phase for which the standard enthalpy of formation is defined.
A relation that defines the temperature at which the value of a property is estimated.
A relation between the standard enthalpy of formation and its provenance information.
The canonical position of an atom in a species.
A number that indicates the amount of an element in a species.
The combined masses of all atoms of a molecule. In ChEBI, http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/chebi/mass is defined as an annotation property.
An identifier designed to codify chemical species, molecules or substances. In ChEBI, http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/chebi/inchi is defined as an annotation property.
A fixed-length representation of InChI. In ChEBI, http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/chebi/inchikey is defined as an annotation property.

A numerical identifier designed to uniquely identify all chemical substances. Also in PeriodicTable, http://www.daml.org/2003/01/periodictable/PeriodicTable#casRegistryID is defined as a data type property.
The data property that represents the bonds between all atoms in a species.
The data property that represents the geometry of species.
An alternative name of a chemical species, molecule or substance.
The date when a web page was accessed.
The value of a property. Also in OntoCAPE, http://www.theworldavatar.com/ontology/ontocape/upper_level/system.owl#value is designed as a data type property.

Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry System. A form of line notation for codifying the structure of a chemical species using short ASCII strings.  In ChEBI, http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/chebi/smiles is defined as an annotation property.
The overall net charge of a molecule. In ChEBI, http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/chebi/charge is defined as an annotation property.
The PubChem Compound Identifier (CID) number taken from their database of chemical molecules and their activities in biological assays.
The spin multiplicity is equal to the number of alpha electrons, minus beta electrons, plus 1.
